body:
I'm not saying he is ridiculous op or something, he could be op in 1 out of 100 cases, but it's utterly annoying how hard you have to try to avoid {{champion:157}} feeding phase which lasts for whole game. Look at his winrate also.
I could just pick {{champion:11}} with samurai skin and start right clicking, while not sweating or showing over 9000 apm for the same result.
The last nerf {{item:3031}} did really shorten the gap between the phase where Yasuo is feeding machine and where he is killing machine. How often do you see a {{champion:157}} with at least 50% less deaths than kills?
I would only pick Yasuo now, where favorable allies are picked {{champion:40}} {{champion:12}}, no champion should be so reliant on other champions' specifics.
Do you know what my friends call him after you nerfed his already miniscule amount of hp? That's right, the Paperbag Yasuo, the bursters wouldn't even want use their dfgs to finish this guy. What, should buy banshee? Oh sorry, can't live with 2 or 1 or 0 damage items like the rest of the bruisers anymore {{champion:64}} 

